From: Kenneth Kasilag <kenneth@kasilag.me>
Date: Sun, 05 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: qualcomm: ppe: add virtual ports for non-PPE devices

A virtual port is a PPE port number past the physical ones, bound to a
net device the PPE cannot reach directly - a wireless VAP. It lets the
L3 flow engine forward to such a device: the flow is forwarded to the
virtual port, whose L2_VP_PORT_TBL entry points its physical port at
the CPU and its unicast queue at the CPU port's queue, so the packet
is delivered to the host on an EDMA ring already rewritten, to be
transmitted out the device.

Add the virtual port allocator, its hardware programming, and a
registry mapping a virtual port back to its net device for the receive
path. The L2_VP_PORT_TBL field set follows the vendor driver's
programming of a wireless virtual port: routed rather than bridged, so
it forwards on an invalid VSI, accepts any address, is backed by the
CPU port and marked active, with learning left off because the
software bridge owns the address of a wireless station.

Virtual ports are an APPE feature, gated on the SoC variant. Nothing
allocates one yet; the device-event tracking, the flowtable and the
receive path follow.

Signed-off-by: Kenneth Kasilag <kenneth@kasilag.me>
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/Makefile
@@ -4,7 +4,7 @@
 #
 
 obj-$(CONFIG_QCOM_PPE) += qcom-ppe.o
-qcom-ppe-objs := ppe.o ppe_config.o ppe_debugfs.o ppe_port.o ppe_api.o ppe_bridge.o ppe_flow.o ppe_flowtable.o
+qcom-ppe-objs := ppe.o ppe_config.o ppe_debugfs.o ppe_port.o ppe_api.o ppe_bridge.o ppe_flow.o ppe_flowtable.o ppe_vp.o
 
 #EDMA
 qcom-ppe-objs += edma.o edma_cfg_rx.o edma_cfg_tx.o edma_debugfs.o edma_port.o edma_rx.o edma_tx.o edma_ethtool.o
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/ppe.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/ppe.c
@@ -22,6 +22,7 @@
 #include "ppe_debugfs.h"
 #include "ppe_flow.h"
 #include "ppe_flowtable.h"
+#include "ppe_vp.h"
 #include "ppe_port.h"
 
 #define PPE_PORT_MAX		8
@@ -246,6 +247,16 @@ static int qcom_ppe_probe(struct platfor
 				     "PPE flowtable offload setup failed\n");
 	}
 
+	ret = ppe_vp_setup(ppe_dev);
+	if (ret) {
+		ppe_flowtable_destroy(ppe_dev);
+		ppe_bridge_destroy(ppe_dev);
+		ppe_port_mac_deinit(ppe_dev);
+		edma_destroy(ppe_dev);
+		return dev_err_probe(dev, ret,
+				     "PPE virtual port setup failed\n");
+	}
+
 	ppe_debugfs_setup(ppe_dev);
 	platform_set_drvdata(pdev, ppe_dev);
 
@@ -257,6 +268,7 @@ static void qcom_ppe_remove(struct platf
 	struct ppe_device *ppe_dev;
 
 	ppe_dev = platform_get_drvdata(pdev);
+	ppe_vp_teardown(ppe_dev);
 	ppe_flowtable_destroy(ppe_dev);
 	ppe_bridge_destroy(ppe_dev);
 	ppe_port_mac_deinit(ppe_dev);
